RT @BruceSallan: .@SmartBoyDesigns - From Eagle Scout to Wild (how would you describe LC) performer - a journey to be sure! Comments? #DadC…
I would describe my journey from Eagle Scout to @LordChristian as something of series of chapters. Like a book. Always unfolding. #DadChat
@BruceSallan I make surface judgements on a daily basis. Always. But learning to look with more love everyday. #DadChat
My music is most definitely influenced by life experiences. I try and let pain, joy, love…all of it, born itself in my music. #DadChat
One of the first songs I released was Poisonous Love. No matter straight or gay, love is complicated! :D  https://t.co/T9lsgCIWbi #DadChat
My music can be purchased from iTunes. I’ve had a hiatus from writing due to working on TV projects, but now back in the saddle! #DadChat

@BruceSallan @dadofdivas @ImLordChristian well said Bruce! #DadChat
RT @BruceSallan: By NOT judging THE surface! RT @dadofdivas @ImLordChristian How should people get below the "surface" #dadchat
If you’re talking about how much I’m in love with @HiThereImBear, then yes, I’m most definitely in love now. ;) #DadChat
@dadofdivas I've always thought getting below the surface is done through nothing more than taking time to talk. #DadChat
@Noelle_Not_Noel Exactly. It's baffling to me. It's upsetting to see people "accept" to your face, and then say something else #DadChat
@BruceSallan What an interesting thing it would have been to see myself, ten years into the future, from a young boy. #DadChat
RT @BruceSallan: Remember that little Christian was an Eagle Scout!  #DadChat
.@BruceSallan Because #Bacon is what many consider the meaning of life. #DadChat
The hardest part of my journey has been the “yoyo” of people and their “surface” acceptance of other lifestyles. #dadchat
There's a lot I didn't know about after the time I came out, but I knew coming out was much more important at the time. #DadChat
I believe some people are born gay, while others choose. Some in the middle. I don’t have a problem with either. #DadChat
My relationship with my family has improved drastically. We have differences, but they’re important to forget to make room for love....
RT @GinaValley: Our kids are our kids no matter what. Rejecting them cuz you don't agree with or accept part of their life shouldn't be con…
RT @BruceSallan: Feel free to ask YOUR question of @ImLordChristian aka @SmartBoyDesigns - he's so open and honest it's refreshing!  #DadCh…
For parents with kids struggling with (sexual) identity issues, I would advise on patience. Love…patiently. #DadChat
I don’t have a strong desire to have children, but I’m not against it happening. If it does happen, I want to be 100% on-board. #DadChat
My 5 sibling’s reactions to my coming out was mixed. Many are young, so have no understanding. Oldest have been supportive. #DadChat
.@dadofdivas It was the song Somewhere Over the Rainbow that saved me life. Those words, on a fateful day, brought me back. #DadChat
As @LordChristian I’ve been lucky enough to spend a few years making music, performing on various TV shows, and modeling. #DadChat
When I first began my singing career, I sang in a lot of karaoke bars. Ultimately the fans came up with the name @ImLordChristian! #DadChat
.@LordChristian emerged as my re-born interpretation of self. The character I’ve always seen myself as, and want to be. #DadChat
@dadofdivas so grateful for the people like you who show others there are people who care, believe, and support. Everyone a friend. #DadChat
@GinaValley I was 21 when I was becoming suicidal, which was almost 3 years ago now #DadChat
The biggest joy I have in coming out is the feeling of peace I feel inside. It’s priceless to me. I can be honest to my core now. #DadChat
Initially reactions were sever to my coming out. I moved, left church and came out within a week – which some felt betrayed by. #DadChat
@JandJDad right?! So funny how as youngsters, we're already so much of what we're going to be for the rest of life! #DadChat
.@Noelle_Not_Noel thank you! I'm certainly grateful the light was found! #DadChat
.@BruceSallan My sexuality was something I was ashamed of for years, so it festered. This is why I feel it so important to talk. #DadChat
What motivated me to come out were intense suicidal developments. Being so close to the end showed me the light. #DadChat
@BruceSallan leaving home at 16 counts. You certainly came out into the world for some exploring! #DadChat
@GinaValley and let us hope we can continue to show love and support where it isn't. You're awesome! #DadChat
@BlackBookBlur exactly. Whether gay, straight, bi -  that's going to occur, and all need support surely. Thanks for sharing! #DadChat
@BlackBookBlur that seems to be around the age I was quite clear on my sexuality as well. Around 12. #DadChat
RT @aDadsPov: .@SmartBoyDesigns - Were you raised in a religious environment and did that affect your “coming out?” #DadChat
I was raised Mormon, so it certainly drew out how long I was “in the closet.” For many years I was too afraid to come out. #DadChat
